@node "Intro"

    This is simple clock or better a timer with an Arexx port.
    Its behaviour is the same of cronograph, but MVTime displays only Hours,
    minutes and seconds.

    You can calculate how many time is elapsed between two events: by hand
    (pressing 'R'eset 'Start' and then 'Stop') or by an Arexx script.    
@endnode
@node "Usage"

    Copy Amos.library and Gui.library to your libs: directory.
    Run it. 
    Pressing 'R' you RESET the counter.
    Pressing 'START/STOP' you turn ON/OFF the conuter.

    Is there a simplier way?    
@endnode
@node "Arexx"

    The Arexx port is called @{fg shine}MVTIME@{fg text}

    MVTime knows 4 commands:

    @{fg shine}reset@{fg text}: reset the counter

    @{fg shine}start@{fg text}: turn on the counter

    @{fg shine}stop@{fg text} : turn off the conuter

    @{fg shine}quit@{fg text} : bye!.

    Make sure you have typed in the @{fg shine}right case@{fg text} (MVTIME,reset,start,stop,quit)

    Example:

        - to reset the counter type in a shell :

              rx "OPTIONS RESULTS; Address 'MVTIME' 'reset'; Say RESULT"
 
        - to start the conuter type in a shell :

              rx "OPTIONS RESULTS; Address 'MVTIME' 'start'; Say RESULT"

        - to stop the conuter type in a shell :

              rx "OPTIONS RESULTS; Address 'MVTIME' 'stop'; Say RESULT"

        - to quit type:

              rx "OPTIONS RESULTS; Address 'MVTIME' 'quit'; Say RESULT"


        Of course, you can even use a script...
@endnode
